oraisa.tiivistys.logic

Class BitOutputStream

  • java.lang.Object
    • oraisa.tiivistys.logic.BitOutputStream

  • public class BitOutputStream
extends Object
    An output stream where individual bits can be written to. The bits written to the stream are stored in an underlying array.

    • Method Detail

      • getBytes

        public byte[] getBytes()
        Get the bits written to the stream.
        Returns:
        A byte array with all the bits written to the stream. The last bits of the last byte may be zeros if the written bits don't add up to a whole number of bytes. This method return a newly created array each time it is called.

      • writeBits

        public void writeBits(byte bits,
                      int numberOfBits)
        Write bits to this stream.
        Parameters:
        bits - A byte with the bits to write.
        numberOfBits - The number of least significant bits to write from bits. Must be positive and at most 8.

      • writeBits

        public void writeBits(int bits,
                      int numberOfBits)
        Write bits to this stream.
        Parameters:
        bits - An int with the bits to write.
        numberOfBits - The number of least significant bits to write from bits. Must be positive and at most 8.
